15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 441 of Title 72, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. There is hereby authorized the establishment by the Oklahoma
20 Veterans Commission of a private, not-for-profit, charitable
21 organization to be known as the “State of Oklahoma Veterans
22 Foundation”. The Foundation shall be for the purpose of soliciting,
23 accepting, receiving, holding, investing, managing, utilizing, and
24 expending contributions of money, real or personal property, and
ENGR. S. B. NO. 530 Page 1

1 serv ices, for use in support of the activities, services,
2 facilities, properties, and programs of the Commission and the
3 Oklahoma Department of Veterans Affairs, as they support veterans
4 who are residents of this state. Such contributions shall be
5 supplementary to any state funding received by the Department and
6 shall provide a means to further assist the needs of the veteran
7 community in this state.
8 B. The Foundation created pursuant to this act shall not be a
9 public body and may receive contributions from any public or private
10 source to carry out the purposes of this act including, but not
11 limited to, gifts or grants from private individuals, companies,
12 foundations, corporations, and others in the private and public
13 sectors.
14 C. Upon incorporation, the Foundation shall operate exclusively
15 for charitable and educational purposes and shall secure tax-exempt
16 status under the appropriate provision of Sections 501(c) and 509(a)
17 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, 26 U.S.C.,
18 Sections 501(c) and 509(a).
19 D. The Department shall be authorized to create the board of
20 the Foundation. The commissioners of the Oklahoma Veterans
21 Commission shall determine the initial members of the Foundation and
22 elect the board of directors of the Foundation. No employee of the
23 Department shall be a voting member of the board of directors of the
24 Foundation. Any voting member of the board of directors of the
ENGR. S. B. NO. 530 Page 2

1 Foun dation who may have a financial interest in an action under
2 consideration by the Foundation shall abstain from voting on any
3 such matter.
4 E. No administrator of the Department shall provide any
5 preferential consideration to a potential resident of a State
6 Veterans Home in the application or admission process due to any
7 prior or pledged contribution to the Foundation.
8 F. The Foundation shall make all of its financial records and
9 documents including work papers, except for the names of donors and
10 other privileged or confidential materials, available to auditors
11 who are performing audits of the Department.
12 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
